tldr: The user requested to implement a database for questionnaire responses, a
  CSV export feature, and a simple admin dashboard with authentication. The plan
  was executed, including schema updates, API routes, and a refactored
  authentication system using Next.js middleware. All core functionalities were
  successfully implemented and tested.
overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by adding database persistence, data export, and an admin
  dashboard. The plan involved updating demographic fields, creating a Prisma
  model for questionnaire responses, and developing API routes for data
  management. A key decision was to implement a simple password-based
  authentication system for the admin dashboard. Initially, a custom session
  management approach was planned, but it was later simplified to leverage
  Next.js middleware for more streamlined route protection and a basic
  cookie-based session. All core functionalities, including database saving,
  fetching, CSV export, and admin login/logout, were successfully implemented
  and verified through direct API testing. The application is now ready for
  deployment with NeonDB.
